From sfalcon at fhcrc.org  Thu Apr 27 22:46:23 2006
From: sfalcon at fhcrc.org (Seth Falcon)
Date: Thu, 27 Apr 2006 13:46:23 -0700
Subject: [Bioc-devel] Bioconductor 1.8 for R 2.3.0 is released!
Message-ID: <m2vesulpb4.fsf@ziti.local>

We are pleased to announce the release of Bioconductor 1.8.  This
release includes 35 new packages and many improvements and bug fixes
to existing packages.

Please visit http://bioconductor.org for details and downloads.

Thanks to all of the package maintainers for their hard work.

Best Wishes,

+ seth

Contents
========

- Release Highlights
- Getting Started With Bioconductor 1.8
- Known Issues
- 35 New Packages
- Packages in 1.7 that didn't make it to 1.8

Release Highlights
==================

- BiocViews, a new way to browse the Bioconductor package
  repositories.  Have a look:
  http://bioconductor.org/packages/1.8/BiocViews.html

- New cdf and probe packages produced by the Molecular and Behavioral
  Neuroscience Institute (MBNI) at the University of Michigan. These
  packages re-map the individual probes using the most current
  annotation sources (UniGene, RefSeq, ENSEMBL, Entrez Gene, Tigr,
  DoTS, and dbSNP). For more information, please see the MBNI web
  page__

  The naming convention for these packages is more complex than for
  the normal probe and cdf packages, especially since some are mapped
  against related species.  The name is derived as follows:
  SPECIES_CHIP_MAPPED-SPECIES_VERSION_TYPE.  For example, a cdf for
  the HG-U133A chip, mapped to the human genome, and based on Entrez
  Gene would be named hs133ahsentrezg7cdf (based on
  Hs_133A_Hs_version-7_CDF).  The same chip mapped to chimpanzee (Pan
  troglodytes) would be hs133aptentrezg7cdf.

  __ http://brainarray.mhri.med.umich.edu/Brainarray/Database/CustomCDF/genomic_curated_CDF.asp


Getting Started With Bioconductor 1.8
=====================================

To get started with Bioconductor 1.8, please:

- Install R 2.3.0.  Bioconductor 1.8 has been designed expressly for
  this version of R.

- Follow the instructions here:
  http://www.bioconductor.org/docs/install-howto.html


Known Issues
============

- The following packages are not currently available for Windows:

     EBImage      GeneR        iSPlot       maDB
     MVCClass     pgUtils      RdbiPgSQL    RMAGEML      widgetInvoke

- Due to a hardware failure, OS X binaries for Bioconductor 1.8 are
  not currently available.  We expect to have OS X binaries available
  within the next three weeks.

- The YEAST annotation package contains two GO ids (GO:0043625 and
  GO:0043626) that are not present in the GO annotation package.  The
  yeast data used a slightly newer GO build.  We aim to synchronize
  these data resources in the next release.

